you to do it, or make it

00:34:01.010 --> 00:34:03.040
happen, than for them.

00:34:03.040 --> 00:34:06.590
And, it's very much in your
best interest, most of the

00:34:06.590 --> 00:34:07.440
time, to do that for someone.

00:34:07.440 --> 00:34:07.990
Now, I'm not--

00:34:07.990 --> 00:34:08.949
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN: Not
in the short term.

00:34:08.949 --> 00:34:10.050
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: Not in the
short term, because it can

00:34:10.050 --> 00:34:11.250
take a little bit
of your time.

00:34:11.250 --> 00:34:13.040
And I'm not saying that you
should be a doormat or let

00:34:13.040 --> 00:34:15.460
anyone walk over you or someone
continue to take

00:34:15.460 --> 00:34:16.820
advantage of you.

00:34:16.820 --> 00:34:18.570
But look for opportunities
to help.

00:34:18.570 --> 00:34:20.630
And these are the kind of
thing-- it's like making small

00:34:20.630 --> 00:34:24.370
bets, where there's no
real house edge here.

00:34:24.370 --> 00:34:26.590
You make a small bet
and some of them,

00:34:26.590 --> 00:34:27.360
you're just gonna lose.

00:34:27.360 --> 00:34:28.480
A buck, it's gone.

00:34:28.480 --> 00:34:29.070
Buck, it's gone.

00:34:29.070 --> 00:34:31.179
But every once in awhile, you're
gonna win the lottery,

00:34:31.179 --> 00:34:32.940
and it's gonna come back and
pay you back in spades.

00:34:32.940 --> 00:34:34.010
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN: So when
