He said what I can do.

00:47:44.110 --> 00:47:45.930
And I said get the hell
out of there.

00:47:45.930 --> 00:47:48.670
I said, update your resume,
start focusing your energy

00:47:48.670 --> 00:47:51.330
into maybe some classes or
training you might need--

00:47:51.330 --> 00:47:51.790
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN:
Don't be a victim.

00:47:51.790 --> 00:47:52.290
BRYAN FITZPATRICK:
--or whatever.

00:47:52.290 --> 00:47:52.750
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN: Right.

00:47:52.750 --> 00:47:54.160
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: But
don't be a victim.

00:47:54.160 --> 00:47:57.230
If you can't change or navigate
the system, start

00:47:57.230 --> 00:47:59.720
putting your energy
into leaving.

00:47:59.720 --> 00:48:01.710
Learn your new skills,
start a job hunt.

00:48:01.710 --> 00:48:03.930
I got an email from this guy
a couple months ago.

00:48:03.930 --> 00:48:05.750
And he said, hey, you're the
guy that told me to get the

00:48:05.750 --> 00:48:07.560
hell out of my job
two years ago.

00:48:07.560 --> 00:48:09.020
And I went and took classes.

00:48:09.020 --> 00:48:10.450
And I am now--

00:48:10.450 --> 00:48:13.090
just got a job offer in Japan as
a product manager for like

00:48:13.090 --> 00:48:14.420
my dream company.

00:48:14.420 --> 00:48:16.050
So thanks for swearing at me.

00:48:16.050 --> 00:48:17.620
All right.

00:48:17.620 --> 00:48:18.610
But this is an--

00:48:18.610 --> 00:48:18.770
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN:
Great story.

00:48:18.770 --> 00:48:19.870
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN: --option.

00:48:19.870 --> 00:48:23.710
The minute you realize that you
can leave, it's incredibly

00:48:23.710 --> 00:48:24.090
liberating.

00:48:24.090 --> 00:48:25.380
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN:
Empowering, right.

00:48:25.380 --> 00:48:26.790
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: Well, you
want to tell Meng's story?

00:48:26.790 --> 00:48:27.920
Meng has a story about
[INAUDIBLE]

00:48:27.920 --> 00:48:28.750
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN: You
tell that story.

00:48:28.750 --> 00:48:29.260
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: OK.

00:48:29.260 --> 00:48:31.820
So Meng, Chade-Meng Tan,
who works at Google,

00:48:31.820 --> 00:48:32.530
just wrote a book.

00:48:32.530 --> 00:48:34.550
It's called Search
Inside Yourself.

00:48:34.550 --> 00:48:35.640
But he has a blog.

00:48:35.640 --> 00:48:39.380
And he talks about a lot of
really interesting things.

00:48:39.380 --> 00:48:43.150
And he wrote a post earlier this
year that said, every day

00:48:43.150 --> 00:48:45.460
I go into work and I do the
right thing, what I think is

00:48:45.460 --> 00:48:46.040
the right thing.

00:48:46.040 --> 00:48:49.560
And then I sit back and
wait to get fired.

00:48:49.560 --> 00:48:50.160
And if I don't get--

00:48:50.160 --> 00:48:50.260
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN:
Sounds grim.

00:48:50.260 --> 00:48:51.900
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: --fired, then
I realize that this is

00:48:51.900 --> 00:48:54.080
the right company for
me to be working at.

00:48:54.080 --> 00:48:55.950
He said if I do get fired, then
I realize the company's

00:48:55.950 --> 00:48:56.770
done me a favor.

00:48:56.770 --> 00:48:58.610
It's done us both a favor
because I won't be trying to

00:48:58.610 --> 00:49:00.860
do the wrong thing for them, and
they won't be trying to do

00:49:00.860 --> 00:49:01.830
their own thing for me.

00:49:01.830 --> 00:49:04.380
Now, I know this is a little
bit of an extreme case.

00:49:04.380 --> 00:49:07.410
And I am very much aware that
not everyone has this luxury.

00:49:07.410 --> 00:49:07.680
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN:
But it's a nice

00:49:07.680 --> 00:49:08.410
philosophy to think about.

00:49:08.410 --> 00:49:10.250
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: It is
a nice philosophy.

00:49:10.250 --> 00:49:13.610
He went on to describe that
his dad lived by this

00:49:13.610 --> 00:49:14.090
philosophy.

00:49:14.090 --> 00:49:16.560
And every day he would drive
home and he would look at the

00:49:16.560 --> 00:49:18.350
government subsidized
housing in the way.

00:49:18.350 --> 00:49:21.450
And he'd think to himself, if I
ever screw up or get fired,

00:49:21.450 --> 00:49:24.420
that's where I'm going wind up
living, as a reminder to

00:49:24.420 --> 00:49:27.090
himself of what he had and
what he didn't have.

