00:49:30.230 --> 00:49:30.450
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: One
more thing, I guess.

00:49:30.450 --> 00:49:31.350
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN:
Recapping, I guess.

00:49:31.350 --> 00:49:31.780
Just a few.

00:49:31.780 --> 00:49:34.380
So remember that companies are
made of people, if there's one

00:49:34.380 --> 00:49:36.530
thing you remember
from this talk.

00:49:36.530 --> 00:49:39.710
And being successful as a
software engineer means not

00:49:39.710 --> 00:49:43.050
just being successful with your
code base or knowing the

00:49:43.050 --> 00:49:44.230
latest technologies.

00:49:44.230 --> 00:49:46.580
It also means learning how to
deal with people and how to

00:49:46.580 --> 00:49:47.650
deal with corporate politics.

00:49:47.650 --> 00:49:49.050
It's just as important.

00:49:49.050 --> 00:49:50.540
And it's something,
unfortunately, you can only

00:49:50.540 --> 00:49:52.110
learned through experience,
for the most part.

00:49:52.110 --> 00:49:53.220
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: It's
efficiency, and its

00:49:53.220 --> 00:49:53.880
effectiveness.

00:49:53.880 --> 00:49:56.940
It's not just about touchy
feely, lovey dovey crap.

00:49:56.940 --> 00:50:00.100
It's about a way to make your
stuff go a lot further with a

00:50:00.100 --> 00:50:00.850
lot less effort.

00:50:00.850 --> 00:50:01.810
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: And
you will be happier--

00:50:01.810 --> 00:50:02.640
BRYAN FITZPATRICK: And
you'll be happier.

00:50:02.640 --> 00:50:03.310
BEN COLLINS-SUSSMAN:
